    "fraction_of_advertised_fp32_peak": "RTX 5070 advertised non-tensor FP32 peak ~31 TFLOPS (5888 CUDA cores * 2.5125 GHz * 2 FMA = ~29.6 TFLOPS). Measured 32.83 TFLOPS at d=1536 indicates TF32 tensor-core dispatch is active (CUBLAS_TENSOR_OP_MATH) — TF32 tensor-core peak on this die is ~118 TFLOPS, so we are at ~28% of TF32 peak.",
    "honest_scope": [
      "CUBLAS_TENSOR_OP_MATH was asserted, so this is NOT strict-IEEE FP32 throughput. It is the throughput a default real caller gets on this driver — the same regime under which the Apple MPS comparison is meaningful since MPS likewise does not promise bit-exact IEEE inputs->output.",
      "Strict-IEEE SGEMM would require CUBLAS_DEFAULT_MATH (or CUBLAS_PEDANTIC_MATH), which would drop to ~10-12 TFLOPS on this die. That fire is deferred."
